        "content": "<p>Hello, I am curious how one can write local definitions of structures into a proof. <br>\nHere's an instance of my problem: </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">structure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dummyStructure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">val1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">val2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dummyLemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dummyStructure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">val1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">val2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This gives the error that the token where is unexpected. Why does let not work here and what should I be using to define a structure locally in the middle of a proof then?</p>\n<p>I think just writing </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dummyStructure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works, but if I have anything more complicated than natural numbers in my structure this'll be very annoying to use...</p>",
